        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer22204875" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14177355201319645550">I am so thankful this book exists. As a child of a black father and a white mother, I was immensely drawn into the narrative of James MacBride&apos;s life. My story is not one as connected to the racism he encountered, but it nonetheless moved me considerably. He paints a tender, endearing, nuanced portrait of his mother and her life and times, and manages to take a deep and conflicting life story and not sink into maudlin recollection or saccharine moralism. An amazing tale.</span>
  <span id="freeText14177355201319645550" style="display:none">I am so thankful this book exists. As a child of a black father and a white mother, I was immensely drawn into the narrative of James MacBride's life. My story is not one as connected to the racism he encountered, but it nonetheless moved me considerably. He paints a tender, endearing, nuanced portrait of his mother and her life and times, and manages to take a deep and conflicting life story and not sink into maudlin recollection or saccharine moralism. An amazing tale.</span>
